Description (stained morphotype): Male
(
Figs. 27, 30, 33
). Forewing span: 
14–15 mm
(n = 5). Except for the black spot on the forewings, the stained morphotype is similar to the male of the white one (
Figs. 27,30, 33
). The male genitalia (
Fig. 28–29, 31–32, 34–35
) is similar to the white morphotype. Valvae and lateral processes of the tegumen are variable, and the range of variability is continuous in both morphotypes.
